@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - identity/Compartment
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired Compartment spec, tracked status,\nand delete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via\nGetCompartment;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListCompartments using filters compartment_id,\nname, lifecycle_state;
:Create the OCI resource via CreateCompartment\nwhen no reusable match is found;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path uses DeleteCompartment with\nbest-effort via GetCompartment or\nListCompartments to DELETED confirmation;
:Confirm deletion via GetCompartment or\nListCompartments until OCI reaches DELETED;
:Allow best-effort completion without finalizer\nretention;
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state in retryable set?") then (yes)
:Request requeue while OCI remains in CREATING,\nDELETING;
stop
endif
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE, INACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the imported\nfield surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields compartment_id;
stop
endif
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply UpdateCompartment only for mutable\nfields defined_tags, description,\nfreeform_tags, name;
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource when the\nmatching field-driven path executes;
:Return success for the ACTIVE, INACTIVE\nsuccess state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nnone;
:Requeue on provisioning, terminating;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: identity
slug: compartment
kind: Compartment
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required / none
requeue: provisioning, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update none;
delete DELETING
supported drift: defined_tags, description,
freeform_tags, name
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartment_id
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_identity_compartments filters
compartment_id, name, lifecycle_state
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
The checked-in Compartment runtime keeps the
`identity` service disabled for
blank/default-active runs while preserving the
explicit Compartment rollout in-repo.
Generated runtime binds through
`ListCompartments`, reads back the live
Compartment with `GetCompartment`, and stamps
the observed OCI identity into status.
Delete is best-effort for compartments. After
`DeleteCompartment` is accepted, or OCI already
reports `DELETING` or `DELETED`, the controller
clears the finalizer and lets cloud-side
teardown finish asynchronously.
end note
@enduml
